  "raw_response": "{\n  \"title\": \"Support Level Breaks and Later Acts as Resistance in a Downward Move\",\n  \"school\": \"Price Action\",\n  \"asset\": null,\n  \"timeframe\": null,\n  \"market_context\": \"The analyst presents a conceptual candlestick chart illustrating a prior support zone (gray band) that held multiple times, then broke decisively downward, followed by a retest where the former support acted as resistance and price collapsed again.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"After the price broke below a well-established support area, it later retraced to that same level, which then rejected price upward and caused a sharp decline—demonstrating the role reversal principle.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: The analyst identified a gray horizontal band on the chart as a repeated support area where price bounced multiple times.\",\n    \"Step 2: The analyst pointed out that the support eventually broke with a strong downward move, indicating weakening buying pressure.\",\n    \"Step 3: The analyst showed that price later returned to the broken support level, which now acted as resistance, leading to a rejection and further downside move.\"\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": null,\n  \"lessons\": \"A broken support level often becomes future resistance; traders should watch for retests of such levels as potential short entries, especially when accompanied by bearish rejection candles or momentum shifts.\",\n  \"primary_image_frame_id\": \"7bKuNphewFY_f009\",\n  \"supporting_image_frame_ids\": [\"7bKuNphewFY_f003\", \"7bKuNphewFY_f010\"],\n  \"related_c",
